gomodel:SYNGO_1804  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: Activation of Synaptic NMDA Receptors Recruits MyoVb to REs (recycling endosomes)\nFig.3: Ca2+-Dependent Unfolding and Binding of MyoVb to the RE Adaptor Rab11-FIP2. Experimental description: M&M:\nHippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos\nco-IPs of endogenous proteins were done from whole rat brains\nElectrophysiology was done in brain slices from MyoVb Y119G transgenic mice or wild type FVB mice (Charles River)\n\n3/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed Myo5b is of rat species: \"Rat MyoVb full-length cDNA (brain isoform) was amplified by PCR from pcDNA3.1EMyoVb (Provance et al., 2004) \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1804" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

